column5: How come the three most active threads since 2:57 this afternoon are about dead fish?  1- Dumping fish remains into the lake. 2- Bowmanville Creek salmon run and 3- Bronte.
I was thinking we were turning into a mechanical/automotive forum for a while there. Dead fish revived us.
its the long weekend and the only ones left in front of the puter dont want to think about fishing I guess dead fish talk does not count
It was a test to see if you're playing hooky?  Michael
its kinda like this "Here's WINTERNET"   while u can

And let the fist fights begin at the one you didnt mention Roy Just for the heck of it, I may go down to flyfish for the last time with a rod im giving to a young lad soon. That sure will baffle a few Using marshmellows and ear plugs on the hook
Not enough carp anglers here. That's why.

Got that right  We fish for something that is plentiful everywhere, grows big, fights hard and are just as inedible as Lake O salmon...The only thing we strip and sometimes poach are corn cobs  I guess you could milk tiger nuts to make horchata
What are you talking about, carp are yummy!
Considering that 95% of the threads on here are NON FISHING RELATED  ..............at least dead fish are FISHING  RELATED.
So when is our next visit to the Toronto Zoo?
Thats the beauty of our site man...Could you imagine how quite it would be in here if we only talked about fishing
That reminds me Roy... Andy and I saw a good Carp on Monday. Seagull was having a good feed...
How bout we turn it into a Birding Site...
But ospreys are the ultimate anglers...So it's still going to be a fishing site
Another dead fish post. Are you trying to bump this thread up. Well okay. You can see that even in death carp are as beneficial/good as salmon.
I killed 4 fish today....does that count?
